word_group.brief_definition: 表达不同意见；表达异议

bilingual.source: They had a disagreement on how to solve the problem.
bilingual.target: 他们在如何解决问题上有分歧。

bilingual.source: They agreed that their disagreement was arbitrable.
bilingual.target: 他们同意他们的分歧是可仲裁的。

bilingual.source: They appointed an arbiter to settle the disagreement.
bilingual.target: 他们任命了一位仲裁者来解决分歧。

bilingual.source: The conflict escalated quickly after the initial disagreement.
bilingual.target: 冲突在最初的分歧后迅速升级。

bilingual.source: A minor disagreement escalated into a full-blown fracas.
bilingual.target: 一场小小的分歧升级成了全面的争吵。

bilingual.source: A disagreement arose during the meeting about the new policy.
bilingual.target: 会议期间关于新政策出现了分歧。

bilingual.source: The teacher is mediating a disagreement between two students.
bilingual.target: 老师正在调解两名学生之间的分歧。

bilingual.source: The disagreement between the team members was resolved quickly.
bilingual.target: 团队成员之间的分歧很快得到了解决。

bilingual.source: She spoke civilly to her neighbor despite their disagreement.
bilingual.target: 尽管有分歧，她还是礼貌地和邻居说话。

bilingual.source: Despite the disagreement, they parted on amicable terms.
bilingual.target: 尽管有分歧，他们还是在友好的条件下分手了。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm not running. Good. Then we have no disagreement.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不会参选。好的，那我们就没有分歧了。

yingyinNormal.en: It was... This disagreement over... My god. You look beautiful.
yingyinNormal.zh: 只是一些费用上的…天哪，你真美。

yingyinNormal.en: In other words, what I wanted most from them was thoughtful disagreement.
yingyinNormal.zh: 换句话说我在他们身上最需要的是智慧的反对。

yingyinNormal.en: It certainly was. I couldn't see it any other way. No disagreement from here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可不是呢。我看不出有别的办法。我也同意。

yingyinNormal.en: The sad thing is, Cary, I was your mentor. If you had a disagreement, you could've come to me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可悲的是，凯里我是你的师傅，如果你有什么异议，本可以来找我。

yingyinNormal.en: In the meantime, we can't allow a disagreement over a single issue to be a deal breaker on every issue.
yingyinNormal.zh: 与此同时，我们不能允许，在单一问题的不同意见成为在所有问题上不能妥协的绊脚石。
